>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Mongodb Installation process <<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<

Step 1. First we remove any file exist with name mongo

>>> sudo rm /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mongodb*.list

Step 2. After that First step we are adding key(without key repository will not load)

>>> sudo apt-key adv --keyserver hkp://keyserver.ubuntu.com:80 --recv EA312927

Step 3. Now, create a new MongoDB repository list file:

>>> echo "deb http://repo.mongodb.org/apt/ubuntu xenial/mongodb-org/3.2 multiverse" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mongodb-org-3.2.list

Step 4. After adding the repository details, we need to update the packages list:

>>> sudo apt-get update

Step 5. Now install MongoDB:

>>> sudo apt install mongodb-org






>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> MYSQL Installation <<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<

Step 1. After updating or upgrading packages install my sql server 

>>> sudo apt install mysql-server

Step 2. After installing my sql server we need mysql client so install it

>>>> sudo apt install mysql-client

Step 3. After install my sql server and my sql client check version

>>>> mysql --version

Step 4. If you are change the security script follow the instruction and command

>>>> sudo mysql_secure_installation

